This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of nuclei segmentation in digital pathology images. Additionally, the paper proposes a deep learning-based method for this task, which is a common approach in the computer vision field. The paper also mentions the use of an auxiliary network, which is a common technique in deep learning-based computer vision methods. 

The paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it proposes a novel method for nuclei segmentation that requires only point annotations, which can reduce the cost of annotation and make the task more accessible. 

The machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category is also a likely fit as the proposed method is based on deep learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. 

The information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category may also be relevant as the paper deals with the analysis of whole slide images in digital pathology, which involves searching and retrieving relevant information from large datasets. 

Finally, the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category may also be relevant as the paper deals with the analysis of digital pathology images, which can be considered a form of multimedia data.
